<BlogLayout
  title="How to Select Your Wedding Beautician"
  description="Tips on choosing the right makeup artist for your wedding — from booking early to trial sessions and reviews."
  date="June 4, 2021"
  category="Bridal Tips"
  image="/images/portfolio/glam-makeup-hair.jpg"
>
  <p class="text-lg text-grey leading-relaxed">
    Choosing the right beautician for your wedding day is one of the most important decisions you'll make during your planning process. The right professional will not only make you look stunning but will also help you feel calm, confident, and truly yourself.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-display-sm font-serif italic text-charcoal mt-12 mb-4">Start Early</h2>
  <p class="text-base text-grey leading-relaxed">
    The best bridal makeup artists are booked months — sometimes years — in advance, especially for peak wedding season destinations like Santorini and Mykonos. Begin your search at least 8-12 months before your wedding date to have the best selection of professionals available.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-display-sm font-serif italic text-charcoal mt-12 mb-4">Review Their Portfolio</h2>
  <p class="text-base text-grey leading-relaxed">
    A professional's portfolio tells you everything about their style, skill level, and versatility. Look for consistency in quality across different skin tones, face shapes, and styling preferences. Pay attention to how their work photographs — your wedding pictures will last a lifetime.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-display-sm font-serif italic text-charcoal mt-12 mb-4">Book a Trial Session</h2>
  <p class="text-base text-grey leading-relaxed">
    Never skip the trial. A trial session lets you see exactly how you'll look, gives you time to make adjustments, and builds a relationship with your artist before the big day. Bring reference photos, your veil or headpiece, and be honest about what you love and don't love.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-display-sm font-serif italic text-charcoal mt-12 mb-4">Communication Is Key</h2>
  <p class="text-base text-grey leading-relaxed">
    The best beautician-client relationships are built on clear communication. Share your vision, your dress details, your venue setting, and any concerns you have. A great professional will listen carefully and translate your vision into reality while offering expert guidance.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-display-sm font-serif italic text-charcoal mt-12 mb-4">Read Reviews</h2>
  <p class="text-base text-grey leading-relaxed">
    Real reviews from real brides give you insight into the full experience — not just the artistry, but the professionalism, punctuality, and presence of the beautician on the wedding day. Look for reviews that mention how the artist made the bride feel, not just how she looked.
  </p>
</BlogLayout>
